    "text": "The Terra Scientific Pipelines Service is used only when the pipeline requires proprietary data that the end user is not permitted to access directly.",
    "topic": "Access restriction condition"
  },
  {
    "text": "The service itself has the necessary permissions to access the proprietary data and executes the pipeline securely on behalf of the user.",
    "topic": "Proxy data access"
  },
  {
    "text": "The service is not intended for pipelines that use exclusively data the user can access directly, even if that data is proprietary.",
    "topic": "Service scope"
  },
  {
    "text": "Statement A is true in that the service facilitates pipelines that access proprietary data, but omits the key constraint that it is only invoked when direct user access is prohibited.",
    "topic": "Reconciliation of statements"
  }
